# --- AI agent project files ---
# Convention: every AI agent's project-folder uses an "ignore-all-then-allowlist"
# pattern. Team-shared workflows (commands, skills, agents, hooks, top-level
# settings.json, AGENTS.md) ARE source-controlled. Per-developer ephemera
# (session logs, scheduled-task locks, settings.local.json, runtime caches)
# MUST NOT be.

# OpenCode project commands.
.opencode/*
!.opencode/command/
!.opencode/command/**/*.md
!.opencode/AGENTS.md

# Codex project skills.
.codex/*
!.codex/skills/
!.codex/skills/**/
!.codex/skills/**/SKILL.md
!.codex/AGENTS.md

# Claude Code project files: team-shared commands + skills ARE
# source-controlled (so every contributor gets the same DART workflows).
# Per-developer ephemera (session state, scheduled-task locks, local
# settings overrides, project-scoped agent runtime caches) MUST NOT be.
.claude/*
!.claude/commands/
!.claude/commands/**/*.md
!.claude/skills/
!.claude/skills/**/
!.claude/skills/**/SKILL.md
!.claude/agents/
!.claude/agents/**/*.md
!.claude/hooks/
!.claude/hooks/**/*
!.claude/settings.json
# Explicitly NOT included (per-developer ephemera):
#   .claude/scheduled_tasks.json   (in-flight cron jobs for this session)
#   .claude/scheduled_tasks.lock   (cron daemon lock file)
#   .claude/settings.local.json    (per-developer permission overrides)
#   .claude/projects/              (per-developer session logs / memory)
#   .claude/statsig/               (per-developer feature-flag cache)
#   .claude/todos/                 (per-developer TaskCreate state)
#   .claude/ide/                   (per-developer IDE integration)

# OpenCode project files.
.omo/

# Other AI agents — defensive ignores so per-developer caches from these
# tools don't accidentally land in the repo. If we adopt one and want to
# track team workflows, add an allowlist following the pattern above.
.aider*
.cursor/
.cursor-tutor/
.cursorignore
.gemini/
.windsurf/
.continue/
.sourcegraph/
.codeium/
.tabnine/
.cody*

# Temporary apt downloads
.tmp_apt/
